<h2>4. Regular Cleanup Schedule</h2>
<p>Set a monthly reminder to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Delete unnecessary files</li>
  <li>Archive old projects</li>
  <li>Update folder structures as needed</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Use Smart Search and Tags</h2>
<p>Take advantage of your cloud storage's search features. Tag important files with keywords for easy retrieval.</p>

<h2>6. Set Up Shared Folders Properly</h2>
<p>When sharing folders with team members:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Set appropriate permissions (view, edit, admin)</li>
  <li>Create a README file with folder guidelines</li>
  <li>Use team folders for collaborative projects</li>
</ul>

<h2>Conclusion</h2>
<p>Good file organization is a habit, not a one-time task. Start implementing these practices today, and your future self will thank you!</p>
